reviewText:
Amazing journey through shadows...

It's about: helping charming little girl (yep, Telltale has created a trend);
solving puzzles.

Why you should play this: fresh concept: switching between 3D and 2D worlds helps you go through levels by solving puzzles, the core of each puzzle is creating a shadow from the object by moving a source of light;
it's incredibly stylish: the atmosphere of the beginning of 20th century, cabaret, circus – all that covered with the thin layer of noire and touching main theme;
it offers simple, but intriguing story about human fears and desires, mistakes and regrets, renown and family, desperation and relief;
you like Portal series and missed to play something similar;
you like puzzles and platformers.
Why you may not like it: you don't like charming little girls and hate to help them;
you fed up with stories about family importance;
you may find ending too corny: the atmosphere is charged with mystery (or even tragedy), but final turns around a fairytale;
it's short: 4 hours to meet credits, maybe it will take 5 hours to get all achievements;
there's no zombies to kill.
Do yourself a favour – spend 4 hours of your leisure time by playing this game: from start to end without break… The feeling of journey, the bouquet of mystery, the world of dreams, memories and shadows won’t let you be bored.

It’s like a flash of falling star – bright and momentary, but something to remember.
